for i in df[' shares']:
    if i>1400:
        df[' shares'].replace(i,'popular',inplace=True)
    else:
        df[' shares'].replace(i,'unpopular',inplace=True)

Splitting for training and testing¶

In [31]:
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
x_train,x_test,y_train,y_test=train_test_split(x,y,test_size=0.3)
In [32]:
def compute_tp_tn_fn_fp(y_test, y_pred):
    tp = sum((y_test == "popular") & (y_pred == "popular"))
    tn = sum((y_test == "unpopular") & (y_pred == "unpopular"))
    fn = sum((y_test == "popular") & (y_pred == "unpopular"))
    fp = sum((y_test == "unpopular") & (y_pred == "popular"))
    return tp, tn, fp, fn
In [33]:
def compute_accuracy(tp, tn, fn, fp):
    return ((tp + tn) * 100)/ float( tp + tn + fn + fp)
In [34]:
def compute_precision(tp, fp):
    return (tp  * 100)/ float( tp + fp)
In [35]:
def compute_recall(tp, fn):
    return (tp  * 100)/ float( tp + fn)
In [36]:
def compute_f1_score(y_test, y_pred):
    tp, tn, fp, fn = compute_tp_tn_fn_fp(y_test, y_pred)
    accuracy= compute_accuracy(tp, tn, fn, fp)
    precision = compute_precision(tp, fp)/100
    recall = compute_recall(tp, fn)/100
    f1_score = (2*precision*recall)/ (precision + recall)
    return accuracy,precision*100,recall*100,f1_score*100
